# Lead Quanta Personas

These are the **canonical personas** for the platform. Build shared services; expose persona-specific dashboards, fields, rights, and workflow paths — not separate systems per desk.

When adding features, screens, or permissions, map them to the persona(s) below and their required feature set.

## Front office (deal creators)

| Persona | Primary objective | Required feature set |
|---------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **Money Market Trader** | Book and manage fixed deposits, call deposits, treasury bills and commercial papers | Trade blotter, deal slip, maturity tracker, counterparty limit, interest projection, rollover queue |
| **Fixed Income Trader** | Book and manage bonds, treasury bills, commercial papers and secondary market disposals | Deal slip, coupon calendar, clean price, dirty price, accrued interest, yield, duration, DV01, valuation |
| **Equity Trader** | Book and monitor listed equities and equity funds | Deal slip, broker details, quantity, price, fees, sector exposure, gain or loss, valuation |
| **Alternative Investment Officer** | Manage unlisted funds, private equity, real estate, infrastructure and other approved alternatives | Subscription, capital call, distribution, commitment tracking, manual valuation, document repository |

## Portfolio management

| Persona | Primary objective | Required feature set |
|---------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **Portfolio Manager** | Control portfolio allocation, return, liquidity and reinvestment decisions | Portfolio dashboard, deal slip review, allocation impact, income forecast, maturity ladder, rebalancing view |
| **Head of Investments** | Own investment strategy, governance, performance and exceptions | Executive dashboard, approval queue, exceptions, breaches, portfolio performance, ALCO pack |

## Control and risk

| Persona | Primary objective | Required feature set |
|---------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **Middle Office / Investment Control** | Independently validate trade quality, pricing, limits and compliance before settlement | Deal slip control review, limit checks, pricing check, exception routing, breach tracker |
| **Risk Management** | Monitor concentration, credit, market, liquidity and reinvestment risk | Risk analytics, ratings, stress view, concentration dashboard, duration, DV01, liquidity gaps |
| **Compliance** | Confirm regulatory and investment policy compliance | Rules engine, eligible instruments, regulatory limits, policy exceptions, waiver register |

## Operations and finance

| Persona | Primary objective | Required feature set |
|---------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **Back Office / Investment Operations** | Raise settlement instructions, confirm settlement and manage transaction status | Settlement queue, document matching, cash movement validation, maturity processing, settlement evidence |
| **Finance / Fund Accounting** | Recognise income, validate accounting treatment, post journals and reconcile to GL | Accrual engine, accounting classification, journal generation, valuation entries, GL export, reconciliation |
| **Treasury Cash Management** | Monitor cash availability, expected inflows, outflows and reinvestment liquidity | Cash flow calendar, liquidity ladder, placement forecast, coupon forecast, settlement cash view |

## Governance and administration

| Persona | Primary objective | Required feature set |
|---------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **Investment Committee / ALCO** | Provide oversight; approve major deals, policy exceptions and limit overrides | ALCO dashboard, exception approvals, performance reports, liquidity, limits and compliance packs |
| **Internal Audit** | Independently review control effectiveness and evidence trail | Audit trail, workflow logs, deal slip history, settlement evidence, exception history, user access logs |
| **System Administrator** | Maintain configuration, roles, static data and workflow rules | User roles, workflow configuration, counterparty master, issuer master, limit setup, asset class setup |

## Workflow tier (segregation of duties)

When implementing permissions and workflow routing, align personas to these tiers:

- **Maker (creates)**: Money Market Trader, Fixed Income Trader, Equity Trader, Alternative Investment Officer
- **Checker (reviews)**: Middle Office / Investment Control, Risk Management, Compliance
- **Approver**: Portfolio Manager, Head of Investments, Investment Committee / ALCO
- **Settle / post**: Back Office / Investment Operations (settlement), Finance / Fund Accounting (accounting)
- **Oversight (read-heavy)**: Treasury Cash Management, Internal Audit
- **Admin (config)**: System Administrator

